title.rendered: 6.3-magnitude quake kills at least 20, injures hundreds in northern Afghanistan

caption.rendered: Residentes evalúan los daños de una estructura tras el terremoto en Mazar-e-Sharif, Afganistán, el 3 de noviembre de 2025. Foto EFE

image_meta.caption: MAZAR-E-SHARIF (Afghanistan), 03/11/2025.- Residents inspect a damaged structure following an earthquake, in Mazar-e-Sharif, Afghanistan, 03 November 2025. A powerful 6.3-magnitude earthquake struck near Mazar-e-Sharif, a major city in northern Afghanistan, early on 03 November, killing at least twenty people and injuring hundreds, according to the country's disaster management authority. The quake, which hit at a depth of 28 kilometers, damaging homes and the historic Blue Mosque, was also felt in neighboring countries, including Tajikistan, Uzbekistan, and Turkmenistan. Officials fear the death toll could rise, as the nation, which is already struggling with limited disaster response capacity due to reduced international aid since the Taliban's 2021 takeover, faces significant challenges in the recovery effort. (Terremoto/sismo, Afganistán, Tadjikistan) EFE/EPA/NAJIB FARYAD

image_meta.caption: AME3774. PETIT-GOÂVE (HAITÍ), 30/10/2025.- Personas caminan por una calle inundada por el paso del huracán Melissa este jueves, en Petit-Goâve (Haití). Según la Protección Civil, al menos 24 personas murieron durante el paso del huracán Melissa por Haití, un total de 20 murieron ayer en este suceso de La Digue, en el municipio de Petit-Goave, al sur de Puerto Príncipe, y tres murieron la semana pasada.
